<Author>HeikeBerg
<Content>quiet gem in a residential area If you would like to have all the major tourist attractions in walking distance or a quick cab ride away, then you are better off staying at the Hyatt or somewhere more central. But if you are looking to de-stress, the Schlosshotel is perfect! It is tucked into Berlin's quiet and elegant Grunewald/Dahlem residential area. In busy traffic it has taken us up to an hour by cab to get to the Brandenburg gate or Potsdamer Platz and even the Kurfuerstendamm can be a 10-minute drive. That said, we have stayed at the Schlosshotel a few times and will return. You get great value for your money. Each room is individually designed with charming, classical decor. I wouldn't stress too much who the designer is, because if I had known before visiting it could have easily turned me off. But it's actually very tastefully done. In spite of all the curtains and carpets it still feels light and playful. The atmosphere is that of a residence more than that of a hotel. The breakfast buffet is splendid! and the staff is attentive and polite. I have seen someone from the front desk sprint down the block after a guest who had left a glove. In the summer your breakfast on the terrace or in the beautiful garden will easily turn into brunch and then lunch... The pool is not deep but it's warm and nice to lounge around, get a massage, and relax. You might be the only in one there all day. 
