<Author>TheHappySpinster
<Content>More than just a disappointment.... While the decor of this hotel is splendid, it misses the mark in several areas and is, frankly, not worth the price. If you're a non-smoker, you will have no where to run from the cigar- and cigarette smokers who are catered to here (yes, there is a non-smoking section in the dining rooms, but you might as well have a non-peeing section in a pool). When asked if there was a place non-smokers could go, we were directed either outside, or to our rooms. Not nice for a place that charges over $200 a room (minimum) a night.The TV program cards in the rooms do not accurately reflect where the programs are (poor attention to detail, or simply not caring), and the DVD players in the rooms only play Region 2 (Europe) discs, which hardly caters to an international crowd.There are no coffee services in the rooms (a standard, and welcome commodity in much less expensive houses), forcing you to pay outrageous amounts for room service.The food prices are extremely high, and you may find that what you want is not available (as happened to us more than once). The breakfast is 23 euros per person and, while slightly varied, is not worth it. Nor is $20 for a small bowl of spaghetti, or $10 for a bottle of water.We also had poor experiences with the wait staff. While they are polite, and completely bi-lingual, we were charged $25 for our Complimentary Welcome Drink, which was later rectified by offering us six finger sandwiches and two small pieces of cake. The staff is always polite when things go right or wrong, but too many things went wrong too often. And at these prices, it really wasn't worth it. 
