<Author>Chris&Debra
<Content>The Hidden Gem in Berlin A late booking that turned into a wonderful experience after searching Europe for a 5 star break with Spa. A hotel of the highest quality. Attentive staff who made us feel King and Queen of the Castle throughout our stay. Every need given the utmost attention without being intrusive. One the the nicest Spa's we have experienced (absolutely spotlessy clean with all you could need) - perfect attention to detail - again staff looked after our ever need before we had the opportunity to know we needed it. Resturant absloutely fantastic and a must do if you choose this hotel. Travel was easy using local transportation - so its worth the 10 minute journey outside the centre of the City. When we had the opportunity to see other Hotels at the same level in Berlin it was easy to see we had made the right choice. Would not consider staying anywhere else if we revisited Berlin or this area. If you fly through Templehof use a Taxi at around 20 Euro - otherwise you will find it hard to find the hotel. Althought only 10 minutes walk from Grunwald S Bahn (plus a short bus ride), its not easy after a flight. Once you know the transportation system S and U Bahn and bus are great to get around the city. 
