<Author>TerenceM
<Content>Stylish Hotel My wife and I just got back from a great weekend break in Berlin staying at this classy hotel. When you walk into the hotel you immediately realise that you are staying somewhere special. There is a sense of history that permeates throughout the hotel, from the baronial lobby to the fantastic bar that feels like an exclusive gentlemen鈥檚鈥?club. We were fortunate to be upgraded to a suite, which was stunning and very tastefully designed, as you would expect from Karl Lagerfeld. We loved the antique wardrobe, the Hermes toiletries and the very comfortable bed. All the staff were very friendly and tried very hard to make our stay very pleasurable, although, sometimes you were kept waiting for service a little longer that you would expect at a 5 star hotel. Our main criticism would be with the food at their Vivaldi restaurant. The quality of the ingredients and the preparation were first class but the combination of flavours was far too complex. Possibly because we are used to London restaurants were the favours are much simpler and allow the ingredients to speak for themselves we found the combination at the restaurant a bit strange and not to our palate.Before you book this hotel bear in mind that you will need a taxi to get to the centre, e.g. Brandenburg Gate was 16 Euros. But every taxi driver knew where the hotel was for the return trip and were pleased to take us back to the hotel where the German Football Team stayed during the World Cup.On reflection it was a wonderful hotel and we will definitely stay there again on our next trip to Berlin. 
